<TEXT>
six us cities three of them in florida have 
been selected as finalists for two new baseball teams 
proposals were selected tuesday from buffalo ny denver 
miami orlando fla st petersburgtampa fla and washington 
eliminated from the running were nashville tenn charlotte nc 
phoenix and sacramento calif 
the national league has said two new teams will begin play in 
1993 their home cities will be selected by next september 
the cities on the list are the best in terms of market size 
government commitment to support baseball and stadium facilities 
in place or planned said doug danforth head of the league 
expansion committee 
