<DOCNO> AP901218-0010 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
aryeh levin doesnt quite know what his title is 
israeli consul general israeli envoy 
im the head of a diplomats group he said chuckling 
with the questionable title of ambassador 
two years after his arrival and two months after the soviet 
union said it would end its 23year diplomatic rift with israel 
levin still waits to raise his countrys whiteandblue flag at an 
embassy in central moscow 
the kremlin has said bureaucratic problems are delaying full 
consular ties levin blamed the demon of antisemitism which 
he said pervades certain ministries and nearly reaches the top 
levels of government 
its a perception that looms large for israel and soviet jews 
both hope to cultivate a deeper jewish presence in the soviet union 
even as tens of thousands of jews emigrate 
we need a developed jewish life said leonid stonov a 
prominent jewish activist we need to increase jewish dignity 
israeli officials and soviet jewish leaders said emigration no 
longer defines their attitude toward the soviet union as it did 
during much of the cold war cultural and religious expression for 
jews and trade and social exchanges for israel now are nearly 
equal to emigration on their list of priorities 
more than 130000 soviet jews have emigrated this year to 
israel driven in part by increasing antisemitism several 
thousand more have gone to the united states about 300000 soviet 
emigres already live in israel 
of the 14 million jews still in the soviet union about 250000 
live in moscow 
jews who remain can celebrate their holidays openly and attend 
hebrew schools in major cities a new law on religion guarantees 
the right to such practices many of which formerly were 
prohibited 
groups have emerged to promote everything from zionism to jewish 
theater last december 250 such groups formed the confederation of 
soviet jewish organizations to protect jews and coordinate their 
activities 
our goal is to secure the survival of soviet jewry as part of 
world jewry said mikhail chlenov a cochairman of the 
organization 
antisemitism remains an obstacle for decades the kremlin 
painted israel as a racist state bent on taking arab land 
in the realm of foreign affairs where the general new 
thinking is like a stream there are little eddies on the side of 
this larger current levin said these little eddies are the 
antiisraeli attitude the concept of a world zionist conspiracy 
he said those attitudes had delayed restoration of full consular 
ties which would allow israel itself to issue visas to the 
hundreds of jews who want to leave the dutch embassy now 
represents israel in the soviet union and issues the visas 
israel and the kremlin agreed sept 30 after three years of 
warming relations to upgrade the delegations in each others 
capitals 
during that period levin arrived in moscow and his delegation 
moved back into the building it occupied before ties were severed 
over the 1967 arabisraeli war 
despite the announcement the state of relations has not 
changed a soviet foreign ministry spokesman blamed slowmoving 
bureaucracy 
levin said ranking soviet officials told him privately they must 
proceed slowly because of an antisemitic mood 
theyre using it as an excuse and they are at the same time 
suffering from it levin said 
he expressed optimism that full diplomatic relations could be 
restored within a year unless antiisraeli and antisemitic 
elements prevail levin said 
they all have their own pavlov reactions to anything that has 
to do with israel he said they have to get rid of this and 
im glad to say they are thinking along these lines but it will 
take time 
people who deal with israel today in the ministry of foreign 
affairs are not hebraists theyre arabists this does not explain 
everything but it goes a long way to explain a few things 
vladimir nosenko a middle east analyst at the institute of 
world economics and international relations echoed that view 
they have an old perception about the role of israel in the 
middle east and im afraid our bureaucracy is very strong he 
said our antizionist propaganda several years ago created the 
basic antisemitic problems we have now 
israel hopes diplomatic ties will increase trade and cultural 
contacts levin said 
nosenko said the soviet union needs israels agricultural 
knowhow the two countries have exchanged visits by farming 
experts and levin said israels agriculture minister would travel 
to the soviet union soon 
the confederation of jewish groups is working to open synagogues 
and may run candidates for the soviet parliament said chlenov the 
cochairman 
there is a feeling that jews were sitting in the far corner of 
a big room and only now theyre trying to come out into the 
center he said 
