<TEXT>
pioneer 6 built to study the sun for six 
months is still doing its job 25 years later offering critics of 
nasas whizbang superprojects proof that simple is better 
after 25 years we are relearning the importance of simplicity 
and reliability and the value of science as the focus of the 
american space program said rep george brown incoming chairman 
of the house committee on science space and technology 
the california democrat spoke monday as nasa and trw inc which 
built pioneer 6 held a daylate anniversary celebration of the 
spacecrafts dec 16 1965 launch from florida pioneer is now the 
oldest operating spacecraft 
the barrelshaped 6 million spacecraft compares favorably with 
helicopters that fall out of the sky and amphibious assault 
vehicles that sink said fred wirth pioneer 6 deputy project 
manager the government does sometimes purchase things that work 
and pioneer 6 is one of them 
the 140pound spacecraft provides lessons for the national 
aeronautics and space administration bedeviled by problems with 
the hubble space telescope shuttles and other huge 
superprojects said brown whose committee oversees nasa 
he said the simpleisbetter view of the space program was 
confirmed by last weeks report from a government advisory panel 
the group said nasa must focus on unmanned scientific spacecraft 
and put less emphasis on the shuttle manned planetary missions and 
the proposed space station and aerospace plane 
pioneer 6 which was 1319 million miles from earth on monday 
has traveled 154 billion miles without a single stop at a 
service station costing a measly fourhundredths of a cent per 
mile said trw spokeswoman montye male 
pioneer 6 was built to serve as a solar weather station and 
make the first detailed measurements of the suns atmosphere 
it collected information about solar flares allowing the 
government to protect astronauts from intense radiation outbursts 
and to predict disturbances that periodically disrupt 
communications and electric power grids on earth 
it also studied the back side of the sun for the first time 
measured solar wind speeds of 144 million mph tested einsteins 
theory of relativity helped track sunspot cycles and in 1973 
measured the tail of comet kohoutek 
to observe pioneers anniversary a nasa tracking station at 
goldstone calif tuned into pioneers radio signal for about 90 
minutes monday 
a computer converted the normally inaudible signal into 
rapidfire beeping played at news conferences at the california 
museum of science and industry in los angeles and at ames research 
center in mountain view near san francisco 
in los angeles officials also cut a big yellow cake which was 
frosted to look like the sun and had a pioneer 6 model suspended 
above it 
three of pioneer 6s six science instruments still work 
although only two can be turned on simultaneously because the 
spacecrafts solar power cells are wearing out wirth said he 
couldnt predict how much longer pioneer 6 will survive 
newer spacecraft have usurped much of pioneers value to 
scientists and it sends data to earth only about twice a year 
because of demands other spacecraft place on nasas tracking 
stations 
