christmas discounting a sluggish housing 
market and a sharp moderation in the rise of energy prices combined 
in november to dampen inflation to 03 percent the government said 
tuesday 
the seasonally adjusted increase in the labor departments 
consumer price index represents an annual inflation rate of just 
37 percent down sharply from the 89 percent inflation rate 
during the three months after iraqs aug 2 invasion of kuwait 
the improvement allowed the federal reserve board to take 
dramatic action to stimulate the economy and cushion the effects of 
the recession most private economists believe the nation has 
entered 
the central bank cut its key bank lending rate known as the 
discount rate from 7 percent to 65 percent effective wednesday 
the move announced about 30 minutes before the close of trading on 
wall street sent stock prices surging it was the first cut since 
august 1986 
lower interest rates help the economy by making it cheaper for 
individuals and businesses to borrow but by stimulating demand 
that tends to increase inflationary pressures 
the fed needs to be worrying about the economy going down 
more than it needs to be worrying about inflation right now said 
economist bruce steinberg of merrill lynch in new york 
evidence that the economic downturn including slow christmas 
sales is restraining prices was sprinkled throughout tuesdays 
report analysts said 
clothing costs fell 02 percent for the second consecutive 
month home furnishing prices dropped 07 percent and 
entertainment commodities inched down 01 percent that includes 
most televisions radios and other electronic equipment given as 
gifts 
retailers are making sales but theyre doing it at discount 
prices said economist robert brusca of nikko securities co 
international inc in new york sale prices are much more 
widespread and floor traffic appears to be much less dense than 
before past christmases 
prices outside the volatile food and energy sectors taken by 
economists as the best measure of underlying price pressures also 
rose a moderate 03 percent the same as in the previous two 
months 
the effect of sluggish housing markets and even home price 
declines in some regions showed up in homeowners monthly payments 
which remained unchanged in both november and october they account 
for 1 of every 5 spent by consumers 
brusca and other economists said the underlying trend toward 
tamer inflation had been masked by the shock to energy prices after 
the persian gulf crisis began 
but in november energy prices rose only 05 percent after 
jumping 151 percent over the previous three months 
the oil bubble has really pretty well passed through now 
said economist robert g dederick of northern trust corp in 
chicago were going to have some rather pleasant readings 
temporarily on the reverse side of the bubble 
gasoline prices rose 03 percent after a 77 percent jump in 
october fuel oil prices which increased 508 percent in the 
preceding three months fell 38 percent in november but natural 
gas costs were up 32 percent and electricity charges rose 06 
percent 
inflation of prices for services as opposed to goods has 
reacted less strongly to the slowing economy medical care for 
instance rose a hefty 08 percent in november and was 94 percent 
more expensive than a year ago overall they were up 04 percent 
other higherthanaverage price increases included 
new cars up 06 but only the third rise in 10 months 
airline fares up 36 percent in november and 84 percent over 
the past three months after the rise in aviation fuel 
tobacco up 07 percent for the month and 11 percent over the 
past year 
food and beverage prices rose 04 percent pulled up by a large 
27 percent increase in fruit and vegetable prices the cost of 
beef pork fish and eggs also rose however prices fell for 
poultry cereal and bakery products and dairy products 
especially in the west it was very very dry and we struggled 
with the fall fruit and vegetable crops said economist donald 
ratajczak of georgia state university but unless we have a big 
freeze that shouldnt continue 
the various changes put the index for all consumer goods and 
services at 1338 in november that means a hypothetical selection 
of goods and services that cost 100 on average in the 198284 base 
period cost 13380 last month up from 12590 a year ago 
in a separate report the labor department said americans real 
earnings increased a seasonally adjusted 05 percent still over 
the past year wages have not kept pace with inflation average 
