workers were 34849 in november up 3 percent from a year ago 
for the first 11 months of the year consumer prices rose at a 
seasonally adjusted annual rate of 64 percent the worst rate 
since 1981 and well above last years 46 percent rate 
however economists expect the inflation rate to subside to 
between 3 percent and 4 percent next year as the slumping economy 
further weakens demand and as oil prices turn down 
