<TEXT>
awakenings is a feel good movie it wants to make you 
laugh it wants to make you cry it wants to make you feel good 
about yourself although nothing could match the selfsatisfaction 
of the filmmakers themselves 
the movie is based on dr oliver sacks book about 
postencephalitic syndrome a neurological disorder that left 
victims trancelike virtually immobile for decades the syndrome 
was a result of an epidemic of encephalitis lethargica or viral 
sleeping sickness that occurred from 191727 
the illness was considered incurable until the late 1960s when 
a miracle drug ldopa was discovered sacks working at mount 
carmel hospital in the new york city borough of the bronx tried 
the drug on his patients in the summer of 1969 
the results were truly a miracle within days many of them 
were up and about walking and talking touching and smelling 
functions most people take for granted without condescension or 
pity sacks wrote of their sheer awe and gratitude for having 
another chance there is nothing alive which is not individual 
our health is ours our diseases are ours our reactions are ours 
 
but the downside was just as strong some patients were 
horrified to learn they had slept for so many years gasping as 
they looked in the mirror and saw their nowelderly faces one 
woman who had been ill for more than 40 years awoke believing it 
was still 1926 
soon side effects set in patients developed severe tics or 
experienced drastic mood swings some regressed to their earlier 
conditions and died others lived somewhat better than they had 
before the emergence of the drug but never as well as they had 
that first summer 
the cases of many of those patients are effectively reenacted 
in awakenings notably leonard l as played by robert de 
niro 
unfortunately the simple truths about illness and aging are not 
enough for director penny marshall big and screenwriter steve 
zaillian the falcon and the snowman 
they slap on a contrived love story and good vs evil melodrama 
using stereotypes straight out of daytime soap operas the kindly 
doctor robin williams the lonely nurse julie kavner and the 
unfeeling bureaucrat john heard 
they recruit the worlds nicest hospital staff and arouse 
leonards interest with a girl sweet enough to live up to the name 
of the actress who portrays her penelope ann miller the story is 
built for applause such as when heard insists there is no money 
for the drug and quickly finds a check placed in front of him by 
the evernoble kavner 
heartwarming may have worked for big but applied to 
awakenings it turns a dignified moving story into a jerry 
lewis telethon mercifully its much shorter 
produced by walter f parkes and lawrence lasker with marshall 
arne schmidt and elliot abbott as executive producers the columbia 
pictures release is rated pg13 running time 120 minutes 
equals 
motion picture association of america rating definitions 
g general audiences all ages admitted 
pg parental guidance suggested some material may not be 
suitable for children 
pg13 special parental guidance strongly suggested for 
children under 13 some material may be inappropriate for young 
children 
r restricted under 17 requires accompanying parent or adult 
guardian 
nc17 no one under 17 admitted 
