the chaotic start of a sweepstakes promotion that 
promised to put an american aboard the soviet space station became 
even more tangled tuesday when the official soviet news agency 
called the contest a hoax 
complicating matters still further texas officials said they 
were investigating to see whether the contest by space travel 
services violated state lottery laws 
the houstonbased company announced monday that callers to a 900 
number had a chance to win six months training a trip aboard a 
soviet rocket and a week on the space station mir 
so many callers dialed the number to enter the sweepstakes at 
299 a shot that they knocked the dallasbased phone system out 
of service periodically monday and tuesday 
weve been rather overwhelmed james davidson senior vice 
president of space travel said tuesday 
the companys glee turned to confusion later in the day when 
tass denied reports of any deal involving americans and glavkosmos 
the soviet space agency and said it was a hoax 
the glavkosmos does not know anything about this project 
tass reported 
