the service disruption he said he worked all night to expand his 
computer systems capacity to handle the volume 
summers and davidson said they didnt know how many calls had 
been received davidson said the system was able to handle 200 
phone calls at once 
for 200 people to call and lock up the system would require 
several thousand people calling every hour davidson said 
summers said the calls to the 900 number are stored on digital 
tape with 17686 messages per tape winners will be chosen by an 
accounting firm that will randomly designate a location on a part 
of the tape he said 
