<TEXT>
alejandro morfin ran his fingers over the 
hairline cracks creeping into the diego rivera mural of peasants 
bending over a bountiful wheat harvest 
these fissures didnt exist and theyre beginning to work 
their way up the art restorer said looking toward the top of 
the wall 
la era is one of 124 panels of frescoes rivera painted at 
the public education department one of the prolific muralists 
major works like other landmark buildings nearby the early 
20thcentury structure is shifting on the spongy clay lakebed under 
the citys historic downtown 
severe cracks from the big 1985 earthquake and the buildings 
structural faults add to the deterioration 
frescoes are painted directly on walls before the plaster dries 
and arent made to move as the building has settled some of the 
scenes of workers peasants revolutionary soldiers and high 
society painted on the walls of its inner patios in the 1920s have 
cracked 
six panels of the national treasures have had to be removed a 
risky tedious process used only as a last resort 
dozens of others have been sealed with cloth foam rubber and 
plywood bandages to protect them from further damage during 
restoration work on the building 
forests of crosshatched timbers shore up arches around the 
patios 
if it werent propped up it would have begun to fall down 
said morfin who heads a team of four protecting the murals until 
repairs are complete 
a jagged crack from the devastating earthquake of sept 19 
1985 splits the north and west walls from the top floor to the 
ground at morfins feet a crack breaks the red tile floor snakes 
up the 14foot walls on either side where murals had been removed 
and into the ceiling 
adding to the problems a huge staircase built in the 1940s 
pulls on the building it vibrates from traffic and construction 
work cracks run through it like networks of nerves to relieve 
pressure weight was removed the building moves to adjust 
the pumping of water to keep the excavated ruins of the aztecs 
great temple dry and on display has worsened the sinking problem 
for the education department metropolitan cathedral national 
palace and other buildings in the area said morfin and officials 
of the governments national center for conservation of artistic 
works 
the building is compressing its working with different 
pressures morfin said 
and as in many old buildings humidity seeps through its walls 
when the conservation center part of the national fine arts 
institute gave morfin responsibility for the rivera murals in 
march onethird were slated for special protection while the 
building is repaired now there are more than 60 
only the north and south walls were contemplated now we have 
to cover almost all the west he said 
rivera began the murals in early 1923 he had spent more than a 
decade in europe then returned in mexico to become reacquainted 
with his people and their problems after the 191021 revolution 
rejecting abstract art he directed his painting toward the 
masses rather than the elite creating a nationalist educational 
school that became internationally recognized 
scenes of peasants and laborers struggling to improve their 
lives meetings of the proletariat contrasting with fancy dinners 
of capitalists revolutionary martyrs heroes and soldiers are the 
result 
since the public education department more than any other 
public building is the building of the people the theme of its 
decoration could not be anything other than the life of the people 
themselves rivera is quoted as saying in an education department 
book on the murals 
on the second floor and part of the third a series of 
graytoned frescoes painted to look like low reliefs depict 
science architecture research dance music medicine and other 
intellectual pursuits they contrast with the rich colors of the 
other murals 
removing frescoes is a tricky business 
animal resin is applied then gauzy cotton and the painting is 
pulled off upside down on a table in a room set aside for the 
restoration project it is flattened under weights when the team 
is satisfied its turned right side up and a steam chamber is 
created to soften it hot compresses are applied and the cotton is 
peeled off gingerly 
its only done when theres a great risk of losing the work 
its a last resort said alejandro flores another member of the 
team 
of the six murals removed one is on display at a museum and the 
others are in storage or being restored 
officials hope to have the murals on display again in 1992 but 
say the project may take longer 
some of riveras other murals such as those at the national 
preparatory institute and the national palace are awaiting 
conservation teams 
dream of a sunday afternoon in alameda park was moved to a 
museum built behind the park after the del prado hotel was heavily 
damaged by the 1985 earthquake that mural was not painted directly 
on the wall however 
rivera also painted murals in san francisco detroit and new 
york murals done for rockefeller center in new york that included 
a portrait of lenin were destroyed 
