had said previously it intended to lay off 2000 workers 
 
washington ap the federal reserve cut a key lending rate by 
onehalf percentage point sending its strongest signal to date 
that it intends to battle the growing weakness in the american 
economy with easier credit 
the fed announced tuesday that it was lowering its discount 
rate the interest it charges to make loans to banks from 7 
percent to 65 percent it was the first reduction in this interest 
rate in more than four years 
analysts predicted the cut would prompt a reduction in a variety 
of business and consumer loan rates 
 
washington ap the united states suffered the worst monthly 
trade deficit in 2 years in october an 116 billion imbalance 
that analysts said would make the early months of the recession 
worse than expected 
however in a second report tuesday the government said 
consumer prices rose a moderate 03 percent in december reflecting 
an easing of inflationary pressures 
the bad trade news prompted some economists to revise downward 
their already bleak forecasts for overall economic performance in 
the current octoberdecember quarter 
 
new york ap the board that makes the nations accounting 
rules has approved a farreaching change in the way businesses 
report healthcare costs for retired workers a move spurring 
companies to reduce retiree benefits 
the new rule which takes effect in 1993 requires companies to 
subtract from their annual earnings a portion of the costs of the 
benefits they have promised to future retirees 
experts say a handful of large companies already have instituted 
cutbacks in retiree health benefits to reduce the rule changes 
financial impact on their earnings statements 
the financial accounting standards board approved the change 
dec 7 
 
