lawyers for asbestos victims asked a federal 
appeals court tuesday to overturn a judges approval of a class 
action in the eaglepicher industries inc case 
the victims who have sued eaglepicher asked the 2nd us 
circuit court of appeals to rescind us district judge jack b 
weinsteins approval earlier this month of the class action 
in court papers attorneys argued weinstein did not have 
authority to approve a mandatory class action for those suing the 
company in federal and state courts 
judge weinsteins attempt to stay and enjoin litigation 
pending in other state and federal courts clearly and dramatically 
exceeds his judicial authority the papers said 
the approval of the class action was seen as an essential step 
in settling nearly 70000 claims against eaglepicher 
weinstein wants to fashion a nationwide settlement of an 
estimated 100000 cases against dozens of companies whose 
asbestoscontaining products helped cause cancer and other 
respiratory diseases in american workers 
the battle over eaglepicher is important because it could shape 
the future of what is by far the biggest product liability problem 
ever to confront the us legal system cases clog state and 
federal courts nationwide and new claims are being filed by the 
thousands 
asbestos was used widely in insulation boilers automobile 
brake linings and other products illness from inhaling asbestos 
fibers often takes decades to appear and cases have been mounting 
since the early 1970s 
